id="post-4394" class="post-4394 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-direct-action category-energy tag-diy tag-grid tag-tool tag-turbine tag-wind"><h2 class="entry-title"><a
href="http://www.thingsaregood.com/2014/05/05/build-your-own-wind-turbine/" title="Permalink to Build Your Own Wind Turbine" rel="bookmark">Build Your Own Wind Turbine</a></h2><div
class="entry-meta"> <span
class="entry-date" title="2014/05/05 5:40 am"><a
href="http://www.thingsaregood.com/2014/05/05/build-your-own-wind-turbine/" title="Build Your Own Wind Turbine" rel="bookmark">2014/05/05 5:40 am</a></span><span
class="entry-meta-sep"> / </span><span
class="comments-link"><a
href="http://www.thingsaregood.com/2014/05/05/build-your-own-wind-turbine/#comments">Leave a Comment</a></span><span
class="entry-meta-sep"> / </span><span
class="entry-author author vcard"><a
href="http://www.thingsaregood.com/author/administrator/" title="by Adam Clare" rel="author">Adam Clare</a></span></div><div
class="entry-content clearfix"><p><iframe
width="420" height="315" src="//www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/eDdL27bP8wQ" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p>Off the gird living just got a little easier thanks to inventor Daniel Connell who has put instructions on how to build a wind turbine for $30 online. It&#8217;s not the most efficient and powerful generator out there but anybody with basic knowledge of drills can build it.</p><blockquote><p
style="color: #000000;">Creating something that can deliver a few hundred watts&#8211;enough to pump water, say&#8211;might not be that difficult. <a
class="profile" style="color: #262626 !important;" href="http://www.fastcompany.com/person/daniel-connell" data-event-category="recirculation" data-event-action="person" data-event-label="daniel-connell">Daniel Connell</a>, who&#8217;s drawn up a blueprint to show you how, swears that anyone who &#8220;can cut paper and hold a drill&#8221; can manage it.</p><p
style="color: #000000;">&#8220;I&#8217;m hoping the animation is such that nothing needs to be left to the imagination of the person following the tutorial,&#8221; he says via email.</p><p
style="color: #000000;">See Connell&#8217;s 52-step tutorial <a
style="color: black !important;" href="http://solarflower.org/tutorial.php?lang=en&amp;tut=vawt#.U12mO61kHZh" target="_blank">here</a> and his animation below. It basically involves creating a template from paper, cutting aluminum into shapes, then bending and riveting the vanes to a bike wheel. The rest, as they say, is details.</p></blockquote><p><a
href="http://www.fastcoexist.com/3029746/a-diy-home-wind-turbine-for-just-30-heres-the-blueprint">Read more here.</a></p><div
class='sharedaddy sd-block sd-like jetpack-likes-widget-wrapper jetpack-likes-widget-unloaded' id='like-post-wrapper-1111807-4394-53835c40b251a' data-src='//widgets.wp.com/likes/#blog_id=1111807&amp;post_id=4394&amp;origin=www.thingsaregood.com&amp;obj_id=1111807-4394-53835c40b251a' data-name='like-post-frame-1111807-4394-53835c40b251a'><h3 class='sd-title'>Like this:</h3><div
